The paper discusses the use of Web-of-Science data for portfolio analysis, which involves analyzing the coverage of journals in different units of analysis such as countries, cities, universities, and firms. This type of analysis is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SD). The paper does not focus on any specific sub-category, but rather provides a general methodology that can be applied to any document set retrieved from WoS.
